# ðŸ”¸ Graphql Mutations x Resolvers

GraphQl mutations ( with resolvers ) apply operation on database ( create, update, delete ) using resolvers to pass parameters  
_Example: add a new product_

## ðŸ”¹ Define a Mutation Resolver Schema

``` graphql
type Mutation {
    #<resolver-custom-name>(<param>:<type>, <param>:<type> ... ): <type>
    productById( 
        title: String!,
        description: String!
        price: Float!
    ): Product
}

```

## ðŸ”¹ Execute a Query Resolver

``` graphql
mutation {
    #<resolver-custom-name>(<param>: <value>...) {
       productById(
           title: "product",
           description: "descriptions",
           price: 10
        ) {
           id
           title
           description
           price
       }
    }
}

```

graphql.query:
mutation {
    addProduct(
        title: "Black Boots"
        description: "Great to wear for important and casual events! "
        price: 89.85
    ){
        id
        title
        description
        price
        reviews {
            id
            comment
            rating
            date
        }
    }
}

mutation {
    addProductReview (productId:"product_c7102e2f-98f9-49e5-b6e1-ace3cd1dfb76", comment: "great!", rating: 5, userId: "Genevieve" ){
        id
        userId
        rating
        comment
        date
    }
}

mutation {
    updateProduct(id:"product_cd996787-0a3c-4055-9fe1-4900a67500e9", price: 50){
        id
        title
        description
        price
        reviews {
            id
        }
    }

}
